<summary>
The <strong><c>&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML</see> element is used to draw the reader&amp;apos;s attention to the element&amp;apos;s contents, which are not otherwise granted special importance. This was formerly known as the Boldface element, and most browsers still draw the text in boldface. However, you should not use <c>&amp;lt;b&amp;gt;</c> for styling text or granting importance. If you wish to create boldface text, you should use the CSS {{cssxref("font-weight")}} property. If you wish to indicate an element is of special importance, you should use the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/strong">strong</see> element.
</summary>
